Key Match Events: Nikola Jokic scored nine points in overtime to ensure there were no heroics, securing the win for Denver.
Victor Wembanyama was scoreless and without a rebound in overtime.
Harrison Barnes scored 22 points and Devin Vassell 19 for San Antonio.
Zach Collins and Russell Westbrook each received a technical foul in the first quarter after taunting one another.
Jokic scored his 44th point on a layup to put Denver up 115-108 with 2:27 remaining in OT.
Pre-Game Insights: The teams split the home-and-home series on consecutive nights.
The Spurs won Friday's game 113-110 when Wembanyama stole the ball from Jokic with four seconds remaining and Vassell scored on a fastbreak layup.
Post-Match Reflections: Wembanyama finished with 20 points and 23 rebounds for San Antonio, but was scoreless and without a rebound in OT.
Jokic had 46 points and 10 rebounds and made sure there were no such heroics Saturday.
Michael Porter Jr. added 28 points and 10 rebounds for Denver.
San Antonio had won two straight before this game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Denver's five-man bench accounted for 18 points and 21 rebounds.
Julian Champagnie was 3 for 4 on 3-pointers in the two-game set against Denver.
